<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
U of H Caeti Demo
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H1>Caeti Demo</H1>
<H1>University of Hawaii</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Overview</H2>
This is a tool for developing Army tank platoon exercises.  You can specify
as little as a few drills to be included in an exercise, and our system will
do the work of finding paths through terrain, placing enemy units, and
writing OPORDs and exercise tables for a <I>complete</I> exercise that
conforms to your requirements.  You can also specify particular subregions
of terrain and particular assembly areas to be used.

<P>Once the system has generated a scenario from your requirements, you can
tweak the scenario by altering your requirements.</P>

<HR>
<H2>Your requirements</H2>
Use the following questionnaire to specify your requirements.  Don't
worry about not answering questions that aren't relevant to your plan.

<FORM Method=POST ACTION="../cgi/-in/uncgi/test-cgi">

<H3><I>At the start of the exercise...</I></H3>
Indicate the platoon's starting formation:
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theStartForm" VALUE="coil">Coil</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theStartForm"
				VALUE="halted-ctf">Halted Column</TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theStartForm"
				VALUE="herringbone">Herringbone</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theStartForm"
				VALUE="halted-wltf">Halted Wedge</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
Indicate the coordinates of the starting location:
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="theStartCoords" SIZE="8" MAXLENGTH="8">

<H3><I>In the middle...</I></H3>
Indicate the drills you want to be included in the exercise (you can
require that a drill appear more than once by entering a number in its
text field):
<UL>
<LI><B>Battle drills</B>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="vfaa">Air attack
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="vfaa-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2">
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="cfs">Contact drill
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="cfs-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2">
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="ad">Action drill
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="ad-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2">
</TR>
</TABLE>
<LI><B>Traveling techniques</B>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="ttm">Traveling technique
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="ttm-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2">
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="totm">Traveling overwatch
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="totm-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2">
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="botm">Bounding overwatch
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="botm-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2">
</TR>
</TABLE>
<LI><B>Traveling formations</B>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="ctf">Column</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="ctf-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2"></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="sctf">Staggered column</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="sctf-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2"></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="wltf">Wedge</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="wltf-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2"></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="eltf">Echelon</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="eltf-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2"></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="vtf">Vee</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="vtf-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2"></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="ltf">Line</TD>
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="text"     NAME="ltf-num" SIZE="2" MAXLENGTH="2"></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</UL>

<H3><I>At the end...</I></H3>
<P>Indicate the platoon's ending formation:</P>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theEndForm" VALUE="coil">Coil
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theEndForm" VALUE="halted-ctf">Halted Column
</TR>
<TR><TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theEndForm" VALUE="herringbone">Herringbone
    <TD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="theEndForm" VALUE="halted-wltf">Halted Wedge
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P>Indicate the coordinates of the ending location:
<INPUT TYPE="text" NAME="theEndCoords" SIZE="8" MAXLENGTH="8"></P>

</FORM>

<HR>
<H2>Scenario generated for your requirements</H2>
The output will go here.

